In the presence of multiple risky assets, it is possible that investors do not simply increase their allocation toward the asset with the highest expected return and instead choose the asset with the highest expected return per unit of risk. We investigated this possibility by normalizing the future returns either by the ex‐ante expected own‐market volatility
